<div class="modal fade" id="editIntent<%= intent.id %>" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="largeModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
  <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg" role="document">
    <div class="modal-content">
      <div class="modal-header">
        <h5 class="modal-title" id="largeModalLabel">Edit <%= intent.name %></h5>
        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
          <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
        </button>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-body">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="card-body">
            <form action="<%= assistant_base_url %>/intents/<%= intent.id %>" method="post">
              <%= hidden_field_tag :authenticity_token, form_authenticity_token %>
              <p>After tokenization and entity recognition, the data gets passed off to the "Intents" module. Each Intent will
                run their configured rules against the data and will calculate an "intent score." The highest score if any,
                will be returned by the voice assistant as the "top intent".
              </p>
              <hr/>
              <input id="intent-name" name="intent_name" type="hidden" class="form-control valid"
                     data-val="true" data-val-required="Enter name for Intent" aria-required="true"
                     aria-invalid="false" aria-describedby="entity-type-name-error" required value="<%= intent.name %>">

              <div class="form-group has-success">
                <fieldset>
                  <legend>Required Entities: </legend>
                  <p>The intent must at least have these entities:</p>
                  <% all_entity_types.each do |entity_type| %>
                    <label for="checkbox-nested-1">
                      <%= check_box_tag("required_entity_#{entity_type.id}",
                                        entity_type.id,
                                        intent.selected_required_entity_type_id?(entity_type.id)
                          )%>
                      <%= entity_type.name %>
                    </label>
                  <% end %>
                </fieldset>
              </div>

              <div class="form-group has-success">
                <fieldset>
                  <legend>Show Stopper Entities: </legend>
                  <p>If a phrase has 1 of these, it will automatically return false for this intent:</p>
                  <% all_entity_types.each do |entity_type| %>
                    <label for="checkbox-nested-1">
                      <%= check_box_tag("show_stopper_entity_#{entity_type.id}",
                                        entity_type.id,
                                        intent.selected_showstopper_id?(entity_type.id)
                          )%>
                      <%= entity_type.name %>
                    </label>
                  <% end %>
                </fieldset>
              </div>

              <div class="form-group has-success">
                <fieldset>
                  <legend>Boosted Entities: </legend>
                  <p>Not a required entity but if present it will boost the intent score.</p>
                  <% all_entity_types.each do |entity_type| %>
                    <label for="checkbox-nested-1">
                      <%= check_box_tag("boosted_entity_#{entity_type.id}",
                                        entity_type.id,
                                        intent.selected_boosted_entity_id?(entity_type.id)
                          )%>
                      <%= entity_type.name %>
                    </label>
                  <% end %>
                </fieldset>
              </div>

              <!-- need a better UI here, for now instructing ppl to copy and paste the order that matters -->
              <div class="form-group has-success">
                <legend>Entity Types Order List: </legend>
                <p> Leave Blank if full string value is what you want. However, given the rules above return true, that
                  just validates the context. The actual entity value can vary. Here you can comma separate
                  the order of entity types and the tokenizer will very it is in order</p>
                <p>ENTITY TYPE OPTIONS:</p>
                <p><%= all_entity_types.map{|et| et.name }.join(', ') %></p>
                <textarea rows="8" id="entity_type_order" name="entity_type_ordered_list" class="form-control valid"
                          placeholder="Ordered List of Entity Types Separated By Comma"
                ><%= intent.entity_type_order_list_string %></textarea>
              </div>
              <div>
                <button id="payment-button" type="submit" class="btn btn-lg btn-info btn-block">
                  <i class="zmdi zmdi-collection-bookmark"></i>
                  <span id="payment-button-amount">Save</span>
                  <span id="payment-button-sending" style="display:none;">Savingâ€¦</span>
                </button>
              </div>
            </form>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="modal-footer">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal">Cancel</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
